args: The Appolonia Cup\nLea Vs The Enigmatic Knight
Oh man, this match is gonna be EPIC!

All hail Lea, the Flower in the Fray!
Due to the events in Alberia, she's
had a long absence from the arenaâ€”
but her skills are as sharp as ever!
But the knight who registered last-minute\nis also amazing! She might even be\nBETTER than Lea!

Time to amp this up with a cheer!
WE LOVE BATTLE! YES WE DO!
NOW FIGHT EACH OTHER TILL
YOUR FACES TURN BLUE!
With my next attack, I will finish this.\nI shall put the entirety of my body and\nsoul into my blade.
And I shall answer your challenge in kind.\nNow come for me, if you dare!
We shall now name our winner and hold\nthe awarding ceremony. Come and take\nyour place before me, victor!
I need no adulation from others.\nIt is enough that the honor of victory\nburns bright within my breast.
Uh, okay? Actually not sure\nhow to respond to that...
I felt something akin to the spirit of\na dragon from that crimson knight.\nCould it be...?
How depressing... I gave all that I had\nto that attack, yet it wasn't enough.
Lea, that was a GREAT match!\nYou were just one step away\nfrom winning it all!
Thank you, Emmaâ€”although I fear the\nstep I lack is a sizable one indeed.
If you worry over your stride,\nyou'll never take a step forward.
I would ask you this, crimson knight:\nKnow you the dragonblood prince?
Your reaction betrays you.\nWhere might I find him?
Okay, slow down, mystery dude.\nWhat are you planning to DO with\nthe prince when you find him?

I have heard tell this prince fights by
shapeshifting, and I know well a dragon's
might. Perhaps he would be capable of
defeating me.
You wish to fight the prince?\nTo what end?
As a fellow knight, you should understand:\nThere can be no substitute for the honor\nof defeating a powerful foe in battle.

Okay, so she doesn't seem BAD exactly,
but I'm not totally sure we should just
let her walk up and start wailing on
the prince or whatever?

I will make your introduction on one
condition, knight: If the prince does
not assent to combat, you will not
force the issue.
A battle coerced is no true contest.\nI agree to your terms.
Then I will guide you to the Halidom.
Merely tell me the location of this castle,\nif you would; I will arrive more swiftly\nif borne by my compatriot's wings.
Holy freakin' snotballs!\nIs your compatriot this DRAGON?!
Who are you, stranger, that you walk\nthe land in the company of dragons?
I am the dragonbrood warrior Forte.
Ohmigosh, I've heard that name!\nYou're the Lord of the Skies!
Enough chatter. Which way to the castle?
If you head due south from here,\nyou will find it ere long.
Then I shall take wing at once.\nAh, but there is one more thing...

Your approach on your final attack was
far too slow, crimson knight. If you wish
to employ such tactics in the future,
you must focus on training your legs.
Do this, for I will brook no mewling or\ncomplaint while there are actions a\nperson can yet undertake to know victory.
Okay, I'd heard rumors of a knight who\nrode around on a dragon, but I never\nactually thought I'd MEET her!
Nor did I. But enough of thisâ€”\nlet's get back to the castle!
Well, YOU seem perky all of a sudden.\nWhat's the deal?
The knight's words have lit a fire in me.\nNo matter how large the final step is,\nI know that I will take it!
...I seem to be enjoying myself? Obviously.\nI will face the dragonblood prince himself.
And that crimson knight has\nquite some promise as well.
I have discovered people who have\nthe possibility of surpassing me.\nThere is nothing quite so thrilling asâ€”
You have some nerve indeed\nto challenge me in the skies.

Hmph. You ambush me, then take me
on with superior numbers? Clearly, my 
demise is something you greatly desire.
However, I have news for you...
It matters not what means you resort to,\nbecause they will all come to naught in\nthe face of my overwhelming strength!
That's enough observation.\nWe can take them now.
What is this sinister presence...?\nSpellwyrm! What's wrong?!
Maintain your composure, spellwyrm!\nReturn to your senses!
It seems your wits are regained.\nStill, what IS this...?
Hmm. It seems the amount of black mana\nwas insufficient. No matterâ€”I will simply\nhave to employ more next time.
That is the presence I felt earlier...\nSo you sneak up on us under the\ncover of darkness, do you?
I'll not be caught unaware again, villain.\n...There! I have you now!
F-flee, spellwyrm! You are his target!
You are strong indeed to survive such\na shower of black mana. Nevertheless...
And to make my strength known, I will\ncrush everything! Every knee shall bow!\nMy very name will bring worlds to heel!
Her reason and memories have been\nswallowed by the chaos of darkness,\nleaving naught but a destructive urge.
Tell me, where were you headed?\nUpon whom were you attempting\nto rain down ruin?
I seek the Halidomâ€”and the one whose\nlife will end upon the end of my lance\nis the dragonblood prince himself!
